+## Run Housekeeping
+
+```bash
+flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <workflow> --keep <N> [--dry-run]
+```
+
+Deletes the oldest replayable terminal run directories under
+`<workflow>/runs/` so at most `N` newest terminal unlocked runs remain. The
+command never deletes the run named by `runs/.lock`, non-terminal runs, or
+runs whose `journal.jsonl` is missing or cannot be replayed. Use `--dry-run`
+to print the selected deletions without removing files.
+
 ## Embedded MCP Server
 
 `flowai-workflow mcp <workflow>` starts an embedded Model Context Protocol
